      <abstract>
        <p>Fashion shoot at Venice sites associated with heiress Peggy Guggenheim; excerpts from Mary McCarthy short story about Guggenheim-like character (special section, Fashions of The Times) (part 2 of 2-part section)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The heiress Peggy Guggenheim, collector of art and men, lived a louche life in ladylike clothes. How did Peggy amuse herself? By admiring beauty, of course.</p>
      </block>
